<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-08-25T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-08-25T14:00:00-05:00" n="20" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d20">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">867n.404Wailing Wall/22: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Consul General at Jerusalem</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Knabenshue</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-08-25T15:00:00-04:00">August 25, 1929—3
                                p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>Your August 24, 7 p.m., was received last night at 10:52 o’clock. It
                            should be emphasized by you with the competent British authorities that
                            they are responsible for protecting American lives and property in
                            Palestine.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Carr</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>